<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Cleanup on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/cleanup/</link><description>Recent content in Cleanup on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/cleanup/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C exit() Deprecated — Replace with atexit() Cleanup</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/exit/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/exit/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-exit-deprecated--replace-with-atexit-cleanup"&gt;[Solution] C exit() Deprecated — Replace with atexit() Cleanup&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;exit()&lt;/code&gt; function is deprecated in secure coding guidelines because it terminates the program immediately, skipping local cleanup, bypassing &lt;code&gt;atexit()&lt;/code&gt; handlers if called from certain contexts, and potentially leaving resources in inconsistent states. While &lt;code&gt;exit()&lt;/code&gt; does call &lt;code&gt;atexit()&lt;/code&gt; registered functions, relying on &lt;code&gt;exit()&lt;/code&gt; for cleanup is fragile and makes code difficult to test and reuse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compiler warnings with strict security flags:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Docker No Space Left — no space left on device</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/no-space/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/no-space/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="docker-no-space-left--no-space-left-on-device"&gt;Docker No Space Left — no space left on device&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when the disk running Docker is full. Docker images, containers, and build cache consume significant disk space over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accumulated unused Docker images&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stopped containers taking up space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker build cache growing large&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log files from containers filling disk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="system-docker-cleanup"&gt;System Docker Cleanup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker system prune -a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="remove-unused-images"&gt;Remove Unused Images&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker image prune -a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="remove-stopped-containers"&gt;Remove Stopped Containers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker container prune
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="remove-build-cache"&gt;Remove Build Cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker builder prune -a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-docker-disk-usage"&gt;Check Docker Disk Usage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker system df
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="remove-unused-volumes"&gt;Remove Unused Volumes&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker volume prune
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Check disk usage&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker system df
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# TYPE TOTAL ACTIVE SIZE RECLAIMABLE&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Images 15 3 4.2GB 3.8GB (90%)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Aggressive cleanup&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker system prune -a --volumes
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Will remove all unused images, containers, networks, and volumes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Check host disk space&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;df -h /var/lib/docker
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/build-failed2/"&gt;Build Failed&lt;/a&gt; — COPY failed during build&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/layer-cache/"&gt;Layer Cache&lt;/a&gt; — cache not found during build&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python GeneratorExit — Generator Cleanup Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/generatorexit/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/generatorexit/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="generatorexit--generator-cleanup-fix"&gt;GeneratorExit — Generator Cleanup Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;GeneratorExit&lt;/code&gt; exception is raised when a generator&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;close()&lt;/code&gt; method is called or when it is garbage collected. It&amp;rsquo;s used to signal that the generator should clean up and stop. Unlike other exceptions, it doesn&amp;rsquo;t propagate out of the generator — the generator simply terminates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;GeneratorExit&lt;/code&gt; is a special exception that inherits from &lt;code&gt;BaseException&lt;/code&gt; (not &lt;code&gt;Exception&lt;/code&gt;). It&amp;rsquo;s raised when:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The generator&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;.close()&lt;/code&gt; method is called explicitly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The generator object is garbage collected without being fully consumed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &lt;code&gt;break&lt;/code&gt; in a &lt;code&gt;for&lt;/code&gt; loop over a generator triggers cleanup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When &lt;code&gt;GeneratorExit&lt;/code&gt; is raised inside a generator, the generator should perform any necessary cleanup (closing files, releasing resources) and then return. If a generator raises &lt;code&gt;GeneratorExit&lt;/code&gt; instead of returning, it&amp;rsquo;s silently ignored.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ResourceWarning — Resource Leak Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/resourcewarning/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/resourcewarning/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="resourcewarning--resource-leak-fix"&gt;ResourceWarning — Resource Leak Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ResourceWarning&lt;/code&gt; is raised when a resource (like a file, socket, or database connection) is not properly cleaned up. It&amp;rsquo;s a subclass of &lt;code&gt;Warning&lt;/code&gt; and is ignored by default. It helps detect resource leaks that could cause problems in long-running applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;ResourceWarning&lt;/code&gt; is emitted when Python&amp;rsquo;s garbage collector detects that a resource was never explicitly closed. This includes unclosed files, sockets, database connections, and other resources that require cleanup. These warnings are hidden by default but are invaluable for finding resource leaks.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] React State Update on Unmounted Component Warning Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-state-update/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-state-update/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="react-cant-perform-a-react-state-update-on-an-unmounted-component"&gt;React: Can&amp;rsquo;t Perform a React State Update on an Unmounted Component&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This warning occurs when a component unmounts (is removed from the DOM) but an asynchronous operation (API call, timer, subscription) still tries to call &lt;code&gt;setState&lt;/code&gt; after the component is gone. While React 18 no longer prints this warning by default, it still represents a real bug — a wasted async operation and potential memory leak.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Un-cancelled API calls&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;axios&lt;/code&gt; returns after component unmounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing cleanup in useEffect&lt;/strong&gt; — no return function to cancel subscriptions or timers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promise resolved after unmount&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;.then()&lt;/code&gt; handler runs after component is gone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Race condition with navigation&lt;/strong&gt; — user navigates away during a data fetch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-jsx" data-lang="jsx"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: API call without cancellation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;UserProfile&lt;/span&gt;({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;userId&lt;/span&gt; }) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;user&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setUser&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`/api/users/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;userId&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;())
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setUser&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Warning if component unmounts first
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;userId&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;user&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;div&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;user&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;div&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Loading&lt;/span&gt;...&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fix: use AbortController
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;UserProfile&lt;/span&gt;({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;userId&lt;/span&gt; }) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;user&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setUser&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;controller&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;AbortController&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`/api/users/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;userId&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;, { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;controller&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;signal&lt;/span&gt; })
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;())
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setUser&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;AbortError&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; () =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;controller&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;abort&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;userId&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;user&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;div&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;user&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;div&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Loading&lt;/span&gt;...&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Missing cleanup for timer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Clock&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setTime&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setInterval&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setTime&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date()); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Warning if component unmounts
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, []);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;toLocaleTimeString&lt;/span&gt;()}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fix: clear interval in cleanup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Clock&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setTime&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setInterval&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setTime&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; () =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;clearInterval&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, []);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;toLocaleTimeString&lt;/span&gt;()}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-jsx" data-lang="jsx"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Subscription without cleanup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ChatRoom&lt;/span&gt;({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;roomId&lt;/span&gt; }) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;messages&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setMessages&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;([]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;socket&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;roomId&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;socket&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;message&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;msg&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setMessages&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;prev&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; [...&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;prev&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;msg&lt;/span&gt;]));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;roomId&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;ul&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;messages&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;map&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;li&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;key&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;}&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;li&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;)}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;ul&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fix: unsubscribe in cleanup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ChatRoom&lt;/span&gt;({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;roomId&lt;/span&gt; }) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;messages&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setMessages&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;([]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;socket&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;roomId&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;socket&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;message&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;msg&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setMessages&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;prev&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; [...&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;prev&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;msg&lt;/span&gt;]));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; () =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;socket&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;disconnect&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;roomId&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;ul&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;messages&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;map&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;li&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;key&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;}&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;li&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;)}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;ul&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="using-a-mounted-flag-pattern"&gt;Using a Mounted Flag Pattern&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-jsx" data-lang="jsx"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;DataLoader&lt;/span&gt;({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;url&lt;/span&gt; }) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setData&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isMounted&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;url&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;())
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;result&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isMounted&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setData&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;result&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; () =&amp;gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isMounted&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;; };
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }, [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;url&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;pre&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;{&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;JSON&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;stringify&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;)}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;pre&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Loading&lt;/span&gt;...&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-keys/"&gt;React Key Warning&lt;/a&gt; — missing keys in list rendering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-hooks/"&gt;React Hooks Violation&lt;/a&gt; — rules of hooks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-undefined-prop/"&gt;Cannot Read Properties of undefined&lt;/a&gt; — undefined access after unmount&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] There Is Not Enough Space on the Disk Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/disk-full/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/disk-full/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-there-is-not-enough-space-on-the-disk-fix"&gt;[Solution] There Is Not Enough Space on the Disk Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when Windows or an application tries to write data to a disk but there isn&amp;rsquo;t enough free space to complete the operation. It can appear during file operations, software installations, Windows Updates, or when the system drive runs critically low on space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error affects both Windows 10 and 11 and can range from a simple nuisance (a few MB short) to a critical system issue (system drive completely full, preventing Windows from functioning).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby SystemExit — Program Exit Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/systemexit/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/systemexit/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="systemexit--program-exit-fix"&gt;SystemExit — Program Exit Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SystemExit&lt;/code&gt; is raised when &lt;code&gt;exit&lt;/code&gt; is called in a Ruby program. It can be caught to perform cleanup before the program terminates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;SystemExit&lt;/code&gt; is a subclass of &lt;code&gt;Exception&lt;/code&gt; (not &lt;code&gt;StandardError&lt;/code&gt;). It&amp;rsquo;s raised by &lt;code&gt;exit&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;exit!&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;abort&lt;/code&gt;. Unlike most exceptions, it signals normal program termination, not an error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explicit exit call&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;exit&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;exit(0)&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;exit(1)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;abort method&lt;/strong&gt; — prints message and exits with status 1.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;at_exit handlers&lt;/strong&gt; — run when program exits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Script end-of-file&lt;/strong&gt; — normal termination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Explicit exit call&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;process&lt;/span&gt;(input)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; exit &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; input&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;nil? &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Raises SystemExit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: abort with message&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;abort &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error: file not found&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Raises SystemExit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: exit in at_exit handler&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;at_exit { exit } &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Infinite loop! Raises SystemExit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: exit in thread&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new { exit } &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# May raise SystemExit in main thread&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-catch-systemexit-for-cleanup"&gt;Fix 1: Catch SystemExit for cleanup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; main_process
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SystemExit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; e
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; status &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; e&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;status &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 0 for exit(0), 1 for exit(1)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Program exited with status: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;status&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; cleanup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-at_exit-for-cleanup"&gt;Fix 2: Use at_exit for cleanup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Register cleanup handler&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;at_exit &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Cleaning up...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; remove_temp_files
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Main program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;main_process
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-ensure-for-cleanup"&gt;Fix 3: Use ensure for cleanup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct — ensure runs even on SystemExit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; main_process
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ensure&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; cleanup &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Runs even on SystemExit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-kernelexit-carefully"&gt;Fix 4: Use Kernel#exit carefully&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — exit in library code&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;helper&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; error &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Bad: kills the entire program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct — raise an exception instead&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;helper&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;raise&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;StandardError&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Fatal error&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="interrupt"&gt;Interrupt&lt;/a&gt; — user interrupt (Ctrl+C).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="signal-exception"&gt;SignalException&lt;/a&gt; — signal-based exceptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="io-error"&gt;IOError&lt;/a&gt; — stream closed during shutdown.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>